Downloaded Ensembl/Ensembl 115 Genomes annotation files for additional species and extracted gene lengths. (14.06.2026)
    For the vertebrate species Gorilla gorilla, Pongo abelii, Pan troglodytes, Gallus gallus, Macaca mulatta, Monodelphis domestica and Ornithorhynchus anatinus, GTF annotation files were downloaded directly from Ensembl release 115.
    The files were downloaded from the Ensembl FTP server and stored under data/raw/ensembl/[species]/release-115/.
    For these species, the chromosome-level .chr.gtf.gz files were used where available.

    For the non-vertebrate species Caenorhabditis elegans, Drosophila melanogaster, Arabidopsis thaliana and Saccharomyces cerevisiae, GTF annotation files were downloaded from Ensembl Genomes release 62.
    C. elegans and Drosophila were downloaded from Ensembl Metazoa, Arabidopsis from Ensembl Plants and S. cerevisiae from Ensembl Fungi.
    The files were stored under data/raw/ensembl_genomes/[division]/[species]/release-62/.

    E. coli was handled separately because bacterial annotations are provided as GFF3 rather than GTF.
    The annotation for Escherichia coli str. K-12 substr. MG1655 was downloaded from Ensembl Bacteria release 62.
    The selected file was the chromosome-level GFF3 file for escherichia_coli_str_k_12_substr_mg1655_gca_000005845 and was stored under data/raw/ensembl_genomes/bacteria/escherichia_coli_k12_mg1655/release-62/.

    The GTF files were parsed with the script extract_gene_lengths_from_gtf.py.
    The script extracts only entries with feature type "gene" and genetype "protein_coding".
    For each gene, species, gene_id, gene_name, genetype, chromosome, start, end, gene_length_bp, strand and source_file were written to output tables.
    Gene length was calculated as end - start + 1.
    Output tables were written to data/processed/gene_lengths/.

    For E. coli, the GFF3 file was parsed with the script extract_gene_lengths_from_gff3.py.
    The script extracts protein-coding gene entries and uses the GFF3 gene_id field as stable gene identifier.
    For E. coli this corresponds to the Blattner IDs such as b0001, b0002 and b0003, which are compatible with the essential-gene source table.
    The E. coli output table was also written to data/processed/gene_lengths/.

    The generated gene-length tables contain protein-coding background genes for all downloaded species.
    These tables provide the annotation-derived gene coordinates and gene lengths, but they do not contain HK status.
    HK status will be assigned separately by mapping the organism-specific HK/essential gene lists to the corresponding gene IDs in these annotation-derived tables.
